FBIS3-57297 "drsov016_c_94007" FBIS-SOV-94-016 Document Type:Daily Report 26 Jan 1994 Federal Assembly Duma Deputy Kovalev Named Human Rights Representative LD2401163794 Moscow Mayak Radio Network in Russian 1500 GMT 24 Jan 94 LD2401163794 Moscow Mayak Radio Network Language: Russian Article Type:BFN [Text] Sergey Kovalev, a State Duma deputy and well-known campaigner, has been appointed a plenipotentiary representative on human rights, Radio Moscow International has reported. Similar institutions of parliamentary missionaries exist in many democratic countries, but it is the first such institution in Russia. The main aim of the new institution is to monitor the work of government offices with the aim of out-of-court protection of human rights, [word indistinct] following up specific complaints made by citizens.
